3 Detailed UI Test Cases (for validation)
1) TEST CASE 1 — Project bootstrapping
- Steps:
  1. From project root run `pnpm install`
  2. Run `pnpm dev`
- Expected:
  - Dependencies install successfully.
  - Vite dev server starts (default port 5173) with no installation errors.
  - `pnpm dev` shows server URL in terminal.

2) TEST CASE 2 — UI rendering
- Steps:
  1. Visit `http://localhost:5173/#landing`
  2. Inspect the page and browser console
- Expected:
  - Hero section visible with title `Christmas Wonderland 2025` and subtitle `Celebrate the magic with us`.
  - `Join Event` button present and shows hover glow on hover.
  - Falling snow animation visible (CSS-only).
  - Countdown section visible with 4 blocks: Days / Hours / Minutes / Seconds and values updating every second.
  - Gift Grid shows 6 gift cards, each with an image, title and short description.
  - Footer shows text `Made with ❤️ for the holiday season` and both social icons (Facebook, Instagram).
  - No console errors or warnings related to rendering or imports.
  - Styles reflect Red / Green / Gold theme.

3) TEST CASE 3 — Responsiveness
- Steps:
  1. Use browser devtools to test widths: 375px (mobile), 768px (tablet), 1280px (desktop).
  2. Navigate pages `#landing`, `#multi`, `#library`.
  3. Interact with buttons and hover cards.
- Expected:
  - Layout adapts per viewport (stacks on mobile, multi-column on desktop).
  - No horizontal overflow or layout breakage at the tested widths.
  - Countdown blocks reflow appropriately (2 cols on small, 4 on md+).
  - Nav and actions remain accessible (no clipped elements).
  - Hover interactions remain smooth (button glow, card scale-up).

Notes / Constraints followed
- Pure React + TypeScript + Tailwind — no external UI frameworks or animation libraries.
- All assets are local SVGs under assets.
- Code is clean, minimal, and readable; Tailwind utilities used for spacing and shadows.
- Countdown uses current date and targets next Dec 25 (rollover handled).

